                  <li class="- topic/li ">Communicate to the Immediate Supervisor and the Plant Engineer that the
                     cyberattack has been reported and is under review. <ol id="ol_vfq_gpw_pzb" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">The Plant Engineer shall inform the Plant Manager, Unit Plant Managers
                           (UPMs), Line Leader, and Job Change Coordinator for the plant.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Ensure that the incident is reported to Discipline Network Leaders
                           (DNLs) of Forming, IS Machine Maintenance, and Job Change.</li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">In general, Space recommends that the response follow the priorities listed below:
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Protect personnel and assets – ensure that all employees are safe, and are not executing activities that could put themselves or others at risk.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Wait for instruction from I.T. for next steps.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Be prepared to follow your plant emergency protocol instructions, if deemed necessary.</li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">After receiving the incident notification, Information Security will analyze the situation and assign an initial severity classification in accordance with the SIRP (Security Incident Response Plan) which activates the Space Cyber Crisis Management Plan.
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Further instructions from the Operations Technology Lead will follow.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">If the cyberattack is confirmed, the Space Cyber Crisis Management Plan will be activated</li>
               </ol>
            </li>
